# Post-Edit Verification

After editing any `.vue` or `.ts` file under **`app/`**, **`electron/`**, or **`scripts/`** (or when changing behavior covered by tests):

1. Run **`npm run verify`** — runs `check` (Nuxt typecheck, Electron typecheck, ESLint, Prettier) **and** `vitest run`.
2. If something fails, fix it. Use **`npm run check:fix`** to auto-fix lint and format where possible; re-run **`npm run verify`** until it passes.
3. Do not consider the task complete until **`npm run verify`** passes.

For edits that only touch formatting or non-code files, **`npm run check`** may be enough; prefer **`npm run verify`** when tests or cross-layer behavior (app vs Electron) could be affected.

When adding or removing dependencies or cleaning exports, run **`npm run knip`** and resolve or justify any findings.

For Vue components: follow vue-code-quality rule and use Nuxt MCP docs when unsure about best practices.
